      "text": "set %x% = \u0022{\\\u0022port\\\u0022:8080}\u0022",
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "Navigation into a type-unknown value yields \u0060item\u0060, NOT an error \u2014 we don\u0027t know the\nshape at build time, so %x.port% is typed \u0060item\u0060 (no guessing). At runtime the value\nresolves through to its item (here 8080); the point is that navigation does not raise.",
